These are Puzzles for 2x4 Level 5

.:: Puzzle 2x4-Level-5-1::.
There are 4 different favourite beverages: hot-chocolate, lemonade, sprite, water
There are 4 different favourite colors: coral, lavender, chestnut, emerald
1. the person drinking lemonade is somewhere to the right of the person drinking hot-chocolate##5
2. the person who likes emerald is on the left or right of the person who likes coral##3
3. the person who likes coral is in an odd position##4
4. the person drinking water is somewhere to the left of the person who likes emerald##5
5. the person who likes coral is the person drinking lemonade##1
6. the person drinking sprite is the person who likes lavender##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |   1    |       2       |     3     |   4    |
| Beverage      | water  | hot-chocolate | lemonade  | sprite |
| Color   | chestnut | emerald      | coral | lavender |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 2x4-Level-5-2::.
There are 4 different nationalities: australian, egyptian, italian, malaysian
The people prefer 4 different types of sport: volleyball, golf, skiing, badminton
1. the egyptian is between the person who's sport is volleyball and the person who's sport is badminton##2
2. the malaysian is somewhere to the left of the person who's sport is badminton##5
3. the person who's sport is volleyball is on the right of the person who's sport is skiing##1
4. the person who's sport is volleyball is on the right of the malaysian##1
5. the person who's sport is golf is on the left of the australian##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |     1     |    2    |     3      |     4      |
| Nationality   | malaysian | italian | egyptian   | australian |
| Sport           | skiing      | volleyball    | golf | badminton      |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 2x4-Level-5-3::.
House: craftsman, wooden, cape-cod, victorian
The people use 4 different means of transport: bus, car, quad-bike, train
1. the wooden house is the person driving the car##1
2. the person driving the train is on the right of the wooden house##1
3. the person driving the quad-bike is somewhere to the left of the person driving the bus##5
4. the person driving the bus is on the left or right of the cape-cod house##3
5. the victorian house is somewhere to the right of the person driving the train##5
6. the wooden house is somewhere to the left of the person driving the quad-bike##5

.:: Answer ::.
|             |  1   |    2    |     3     |   4    |
| House        | wooden | craftsman | cape-cod     | victorian |
| Transport   | car  | train   | quad-bike | bus    |

